The paper discusses the use of Geographical Information Systems (GIS) for ocean modelling, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the production of computational meshes, which involves computational geometry (cs.CE) and data management (cs.DB). The use of PyRDM library for publishing meshes to online repositories falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these meshes for solving equations of motion, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
